        <details class=''>
          <summary>How does it Work?</summary>
          <p>Each round of the competition requires the candidate to explore and communicate what they care about, why they care and how they plan to make a difference if empowered financially.</p>

          <p>The Founders of Charitable Heroes personally guarantee that the winner will be able to give away $300 each year for their rest of their lives. How do we do this? It's simple, every year, Mike Hurley, Matt Stelmaszek and Mark Spiegel (the Founders) each make a personal deposit of $100 into the Charitable Heroes, L3C bank account and the winner of the competition works with the Founders to give this $300 away to a cause, organization or person they care about. </p>

           <p>All registration fees are kept inside Charitable Heroes, L3C to cover the expenses (time material and technology) required to provide this great educational experience via the competition. </p>

          <p>The selection process occurs throughout the course of the competition over three rounds. During each round a judge is assigned to Candidates. The submission of the candidate is scored during each round on a scale of 0-100 and feedback is provided by the judge. Candidates are eliminated after each round and one winner is chosen.</p>
        </details>
      </li>
      <li>
        <details class=''>
          <summary>About the Registration Fees?</summary>
           <p>All registration fees are kept inside Charitable Heroes, L3C to cover our expenses (time, materials and technology), these funds are needed to provide our educational experience via the competition. Charitable Heroes, L3C offers access to our tools and staff that make our educational competition happen in exchange for the registration fee. Registration fees are not donations. Charitable Heroes, L3C is not a non-profit and your registration fee is NOT tax deductible. No funds from registration fees are ever funnelled through to a charitable organization or any other organiztion.</p>
         
        </details>
      </li>
      <li>
        <details class=''>
          <summary>What does each round look like?</summary>
          <b>Round One</b>
          <p>Charitable Heroes is colloborating with a New York venture called Ziggeo to make this a fun, sucessful round one. When it's time for round one, we will notify everyone via email to invite you to upload a two minute video telling us who you are, where you're from, and the person, cause or organization you want to help today.</p>
          <p>Charitable Heroes will ask you if you are okay with us sharing your video. If so, we share your video on our YouTube channel for everyone to vote on. A combination of public votes and our judges reviews will decide who moves onto round two. A combination of Charitable Heroes founders, volunteers and judges will individually review every video submitted. A maximum of 1000 entries will move on to round two. Read more about what we are looking for here.</p>
          <br/>
          <b>Round Two</b>
          <p>This round requires a deep dive into the cause, organization or person you desire to help. We again ask you to we provide a link for you to asnwer these questions via an online form. Our judges will invidividually review all submissions and score individauls. A maximum of 100 entrants will move onto round three.</p>
          <br/>
          <b>Round Three</b>
          <p>The final round will consists of multiple interviews with our judges. Only one winner will be chosen to receive charitable superpowers.</p>
        </details>
      </li>
      <li class=''>
        <details class=''>
          <summary>What do I get if I win?</summary>
